{"step_index":6,"source":"MODEL","type":"VIEW_FILE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-06-07T18:05:01Z","content":"Created At: 2026-06-07T18:05:01Z\nCompleted At: 2026-06-07T18:05:01Z\nFile Path: `file:///f:/a/biology/PROJECT_MAP.md`\nTotal Lines: 57\nTotal Bytes: 4181\nShowing lines 1 to 57\nThe following code has been modified to include a line number before every line, in the format: <line_number>: <original_line>. Please note that any changes targeting the original code should remove the line number, colon, and leading space.\n1: # PROJECT MAP - Biotech Biology Educational Application\n2: \n3: ## [TECH_STACK]\n4: - **Core Framework**: React 19.0.1 (Single-page app structured as a native mobile shell)\n5: - **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4.1.14 (Highly curated, modern gradients, deep-space dark mode, glassmorphism)\n6: - **Icons**: Lucide React v0.546.0\n7: - **Animations**: Motion (Framer Motion) v12.23.24\n8: - **Build Tool**: Vite v6.2.3\n9: - **Language**: TypeScript v5.8.2\n10: \n11: ## [SYSTEM_FLOW]\n12: The application implements a smooth, high-fidelity 10-screen Android-like mobile workflow:\n13: 1. **Screen 1: Student Profile & Registration** (`student-profile`)\n14:    - Profile image upload/avatar selector, Name & Email registration/edit, Class Rank representation.\n15:    - Dark/Light Mode toggle, Language selector, and Premium Purchase status indicator.\n16: 2. **Screen 2: Main Dashboard & Settings** (`main-dashboard`)\n17:    - Course overview, overall progress, daily streak tracker, and primary entry points to units.\n18:    - Core settings, notifications preview, and Premium Upgrade call-to-action.\n19: 3. **Screen 3: Units Overview Navigation** (`units-navigation`)\n20:    - Yemeni Secondary Syllabus Units (Unit 1: Nervous Coordination - 10 lessons, Unit 2: Molecular Biology - 3 lessons).\n21:    - Clear indicators of locked/unlocked progress.\n22: 4. **Screen 4: Interactive Lesson Mind Map** (`lesson-mind-map`)\n23:    - Visual nodes connecting the biological structures (e.g. Amoeba protoplasm, Paramecium cilia, Hydra nerve net).\n24:    - Interactive detail cards for clicked nodes.\n25: 5. **Screen 5: Lesson Explanations & Details** (`les\n<truncated 802 bytes>\nediate explanation feedback and a dynamic score meter.\n35: 10. **Screen 10: Ministry Past Exams** (`ministry-exams`)\n36:     - Archive of Yemeni Ministry biology exams from previous years (2022, 2023, 2024), PDF mock links, and timer simulator.\n37: \n38: ## [ARCHITECTURE]\n39: - **App Shell**: Single-page navigation controller in `App.tsx` handling screen transitions (`ScreenId`) with backward/forward sliding animations.\n40: - **State Store**: LocalStorage-backed state sync for student profile information, purchase status, dark mode, language, and quiz high scores.\n41: - **Component Design**: Highly focused, responsive files using a modern mobile mockup viewport frame to guarantee realistic mobile fidelity.\n42: \n43: ## [ORPHANS & PENDING]\n44: *(No pending items or orphaned files. Everything has been fully implemented, integrated, and validated!)*\n45: - `[x]` Screen 1: Registration Profile and Premium Unlock (`StudentProfileScreen.tsx`)\n46: - `[x]` Screen 2: Welcome bento dashboard and streak counts (`MainDashboardScreen.tsx`)\n47: - `[x]` Screen 3: Units syllabus and premium locked gating (`UnitsNavigationScreen.tsx`)\n48: - `[x]` Screen 4: Interactive mind map with connection lines (`MindMapScreen.tsx`)\n49: - `[x]` Screen 5: Expandable accordions with terms dictionary (`LessonDetailsScreen.tsx`)\n50: - `[x]` Screen 6: Labeled diagram gallery slider with zoom triggers (`IllustrativeImagesScreen.tsx`)\n51: - `[x]` Screen 7: Active video markers with study notebooks (`LessonVideoScreen.tsx`)\n52: - `[x]` Screen 8: Gold key summaries and 3D flipped recall cards (`LessonSummaryScreen.tsx`)\n53: - `[x]` Screen 9: Full MCQ and T/F scoring test engine (`BiologyQuizScreen.tsx`)\n54: - `[x]` Screen 10: Timer simulator (180 min) for Ministry Past Exams (`MinistryExamsScreen.tsx`)\n55: - `[x]` Routing animations and state synchronization shell (`App.tsx`)\n56: - `[x]` Fully translated and bilingual (Arabic & English) static keys (`translations.ts`)\n57: \nThe above content shows the entire, complete file contents of the requested file.\n"}
